PHASE 1 — Put your local folders into GitHub

You already have repo:
👉 https://github.com/smunaver/itechash-cicd.git

Now we connect your local code (D:\itechash) to Git.

Step 1: Open terminal in your folder
cd D:\itechash
Step 2: Initialize Git
git init
Step 3: Connect to your GitHub repo
git remote add origin https://github.com/smunaver/itechash-cicd.git
Step 4: Add all your folders

(THIS includes all your APIs like ApiGateway, Payroll, etc.)

git add .
Step 5: Commit
git commit -m "Initial commit - all APIs"
Step 6: Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

✅ Now your code is in GitHub


